Breaks: ukui-settings-daemon (<< 1.11.0),
Provides: x-session-manager,
Description: Session manager of the UKUI desktop environment
 This package contains a session that can be started from a display
 manager such as UIDM. It will load all necessary applications for a
 full-featured user session.
 .
 The session manager also features the ability to save a running session
 and restore it later.
 .
 This version is configured to start the UKUI desktop, based on the
 UKUI panel.

Package: debian-ukui-default-settings
Breaks: ukui-session-manager (<< 1.10.2-4~),
Architecture: all
Depends: desktop-file-utils,
         ${misc:Depends},
Suggests: ukui-desktop-environment-core (>= 1.10.0),
Conflicts: ubuntu-ukui-default-settings,
Description: Default settings for UKUI on Debian
 This package comes together with ukui-session-manager as provided by upstream
 but does a little tweaking here and there to provide best experience of the
 UKUI desktop environment on Debian systems.
